
                                                               byte-position


    FUNCTION
    byte-position  -  get the position from a byte specifier

    USAGE
    byte-position bytespec

    DESCRIPTION
    Returns an integer representing  the  position  component  of  the  byte
    specifier BYTESPEC.  The following identity holds:

    (byte-position (byte s p)) = p

    EXAMPLES
    (byte-position (byte 4 1)) => 1
    (byte-position (byte 6 2)) => 2

    SEE ALSO
    CLtL 12:226, byte, byte-size, deposit-field, dpb, ldb, ldb-test, mask-
    field











































